e act of spying to an excessive intensification of listening. At the heart of listening Szendy locates the ear of the Other that manifests itself as the originary division of a “split-hearing” that turns the drive for mastery and surveillance into the death drive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aAesthetics. 0aEspionage. 0aMotion picturesxAesthetics. 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 0aOpera. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aBentham.  aCoppola.  aDeleuze.  aDerrida.  aFoucault.  aKafka.  aMozart.  aOrpheus.  aespionage.  asurveillance.1 aVégső, Roland.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311072900940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082327398040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823273980423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823273980.jpg  a978-3-11-072900-9  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK